      "correct": "B",
      "explanations": {
        "A": "Electrons flow through the metal wire, not through the salt bridge solution.",
        "B": "Correct. The salt bridge allows ions to migrate so charge does not build up in either half-cell. This permits continued electron flow in the external circuit.",
        "C": "Chemical energy comes from the redox reaction, not the salt bridge itself.",
        "D": "Copper plating occurs at the cathode surface, not by the salt bridge directly depositing copper on zinc."
      },
