    {
      "id": "cp_nernst2_009",
      "passage": null,
      "stem": "Which quantity is most directly related to maximum electrical work from a galvanic cell?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "\u0394G = \u2212nFEcell"
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "pH = pKa + log(A\u2212/HA)"
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "PV = nRT"
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "\u03bb = h/p"
        }
      ],
      "correct": "A",
      "explanations": {
        "A": "Correct. For electrochemical cells, Gibbs free energy and cell potential are linked by \u0394G = \u2212nFEcell. A positive Ecell corresponds to negative \u0394G for the spontaneous galvanic reaction.",
        "B": "The Henderson-Hasselbalch equation describes buffers, not electrical work from redox reactions.",
        "C": "The ideal gas law relates gas state variables, not redox free energy.",
        "D": "The de Broglie relation concerns matter wavelength, not battery work."
      },
      "topic": "Electrochemistry II: Nernst Equation & Batteries",
